<h2>About</h2>

<p>
This is an experiment to demonstrate how to deploy a Middleman website to Github Pages
using Github Actions.
</p>

<h2>How to</h2>

<p>
  <ol>
    <li>Add an action named deploy that builds this website.</li>
    <li>Apply this action to the repo: https://github.com/marketplace/actions/deploy-to-github-pages</li>
    <li><a href="https://help.github.com/en/github/authenticating-to-github/creating-a-personal-access-token-for-the-command-line">Add a personal acces token</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://help.github.com/en/actions/automating-your-workflow-with-github-actions/creating-and-using-encrypted-secrets">Add this personal access token as a secret to the repository</a></li>
    <li>Push a new commit to Github</li>
  </ol>
</p>

